ook<ref name=\"April6\">In command from April 6.</ref>\n* [[3rd Independent Battery Wisconsin Light Artillery|Connecticut Light Artillery, 3rd Battery]]: Cpt Thomas S. Gilbert\n|-\n| Artillery Reserve\n<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[William Hays (general)|William Hays]]<ref name=\"April6\" />\n|\n* [[2nd Maine Battery|Maine Light Artillery, 2nd Battery (B)]]: Cpt Charles E. Stubbs\n* [[3rd Maine Battery|Maine Light Artillery, 3rd Battery (C)]]: Cpt Ezekiel R. Mayo\n* [[4th Maine Battery|Maine Light Artillery, 4th Battery (D)]]:<ref>Attached from VI Corps.</ref> Cpt Charles W. White\n* [[6th Maine Battery|Maine Light Artillery, 6th Battery (F)]]:<ref>Attached from II Corps.</ref> Cpt William H. Rogers\n* [[12th New York Light Artillery|New York Light Artillery, 12th Battery]]: Cpt Charles A. Clark\n* [[Battery H, 1st Ohio Light Artillery|1st Ohio Light Artillery, Battery H]]: Cpt Stephen W. Dorsey\n* 1st Pennsylvania Light Artillery, Battery F: Lt John F. Campbell\n* [[Battery E, 1st Rhode Island Light Artillery|1st Rhode Island Light Artillery, Battery E]]: Lt Ezra K. Parker\n* [[Vermont Light Artillery Batteries#3rd Vermont Battery|Vermont Light Artillery, 3rd Battery]]: Cpt Romeo H. Start\n|}\n \n====[[II Corps (Union Army)|II Corps]]====\nMG [[Andrew A. Humphreys]]\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:25%;\"|Division\n! style=\"width:25%;\"|Brigade\n! Regiments and others\n|-\n| rowspan=4 |\nFirst Division\n\n<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBvt MG [[Nelson A. Miles]]\n[[File:IIcorpsbadge1.png|frameless|left]]\n| 1st Brigade\n<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol George W. Scott\n<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol George N. Macy\n|\n* [[26th Michigan Volunteer Infantry Regiment|26th Michigan]]: Cpt Lucius H. Ives\n* [[5th New Hampshire Volunteer Infantry|5th New Hampshire]] (battalion): Ltc Welcome A. Crafts\n* [[2nd New York Heavy Artillery Regiment|2nd New York Heavy Artillery]]: Maj Oscar F. Hulser\n* [[61st New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|61st New York]]: Maj George W. Schaffer\n* [[81st Pennsylvania Infantry|81st Pennsylvania]]: Ltc William Wilson\n* [[140th Pennsylvania Infantry|140th Pennsylvania]]: Cpt William A. F. Stockton\n|-\n| [[Irish Brigade (U.S.)|2nd Brigade]]\n<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Robert Nugent (officer)|Robert Nugent]]\n|\n* [[28th Regiment Massachusetts Volunteer Infantry|28th Massachusetts]] (5 companies): Cpt Patrick H. Bird\n* [[63rd New York Infantry|63rd New York]] (6 companies): Cpt William H. Terwilliger\n* [[69th Infantry Regiment (New York)|69th New York]]: Ltc James J. Smith\n* [[88th New York Infantry|88th New York]] (5 companies): Ltc Denis F. Burke\n* [[4th New York Heavy Artillery Regiment|4th New York Heavy Artillery]]: Maj Seward F. Gould\n|-\n| 3rd Brigade\n<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBvt BG Henry J. Madill ('''w''', April 2)\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBvt BG [[Clinton D. MacDougall]]\n|\n* [[7th New York Veteran Infantry Regiment|7th New York Veteran]]: Ltc Anthony Pokorny\n* [[39th New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|39th New York]]: Col Augustus Funk ('''w''', March 31), Maj John M. Hyde\n* [[52nd New York Volunteer Infantry|52nd New York]]: Ltc Henry M. Karples,<ref>Temporarily disabled April 2.</ref> Maj Henry P. Ritzius, Ltc Henry M. Karples\n* [[111th New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|111th New York]]: BG Clinton D. MacDougall\n* [[125th New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|125th New York]]: Ltc Joseph Hyde\n* [[126th New York Volunteer Infantry|126th New York]] (battalion): Cpt John B. Geddis ('''w''', April 2), Cpt I. Hart Wilder\n|-\n| 4th Brigade\n<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBvt BG John Ramsey\n|\n* [[64th New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|64th New York]]: Ltc William Glenny\n* [[66th New York Volunteer Infantry|66th New York]]: Cpt Nathaniel P. Lane\n* [[53rd Pennsylvania Infantry|53rd Pennsylvania]]: Col [[William M. Mintzer]]\n* [[116th Pennsylvania Infantry|116th Pennsylvania]]:  Maj David W. Megraw ('''w''', March 31), Cpt John R. Weltner\n* [[145th Pennsylvania Infantry|145th Pennsylvania]]: Cpt James H. Hamlin\n* [[148th Pennsylvania Infantry|148th Pennsylvania]]: Cpt Alfred A. Rhinehart ('''w''', March 31)\n* [[183rd Pennsylvania Infantry|183rd Pennsylvania]]: Col George T. Egbert\n|-\n| rowspan=4 |\nSecond Division\n\n<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[William Hays (general)|William Hays]]<ref>Assigned to command of Artillery Reserve April 6.</ref>\n<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Thomas A. Smyth]]\n<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBvt MG [[Francis C. Barlow]]<ref>Assigned April 6.</ref>\n[[File:IIcorpsbadge2.png|frameless|left]]\n| 1st Brigade\n<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol William A. Olmsted\n|\n* [[19th Maine Volunteer Infantry Regiment|19th Maine]]: Col Isaac W. Starbird ('''w''', April 7)\n* [[19th Regiment Massachusetts Volunteer Infantry|19th Massachusetts]]: Cpt Charles S. Palmer\n* [[20th Regiment Massachusetts Volunteer Infantry|20th Massachusetts]]: Ltc [[Arthur R. Curtis]]\n* [[7th Michigan Volunteer Infantry Regiment|7th Michigan]]: Ltc George W. La Point\n* [[1st Minnesota Volunteer Infantry Battalion|1st Minnesota Battalion]] (2 companies): Cpt Frank Houston\n* [[59th New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|59th New York]] (battalion): Cpt [[William Ludgate]]\n* [[82nd New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|82nd New York]] (battalion & four companies from the [[2nd New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|2nd New York]])\n* [[152nd New York Volunteer Infantry|152nd New York]]: Maj James E. Curtiss\n* [[184th Pennsylvania Infantry|184th Pennsylvania]]: Col [[John Hubler Stover]]\n* [[36th Wisconsin Volunteer Infantry Regiment|36th Wisconsin]]: Ltc Clement E. Warner\n|-\n| 2nd Brigade\n<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol James Patrick McIvor\n|\n* [[8th New York Heavy Artillery Regiment|8th New York Heavy Artillery]]: Col Joel B. Baker\n* [[155th New York Volunteer Infantry|155th New York]]: Cpt Michael Doheny\n* [[164th New York Volunteer Infantry|164th New York]]: Cpt Timothy J. Burke\n* [[170th New York Volunteer Infantry|170th New York]]: Cpt John Mitchell\n* [[