ode Island Light Artillery, Battery E]]: Lt Ezra K. Parker\n* [[Vermont Light Artillery Batteries#3rd Vermont Battery|Vermont Light Artillery, 3rd Battery]]: Cpt Romeo H. Start\n|}\n \n====[[II Corps (Union Army)|II Corps]]====\nMG [[Andrew A. Humphreys]]\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:25%;\"|Division\n! style=\"width:25%;\"|Brigade\n! Regiments and others\n|-\n| rowspan=4 |\nFirst Division\n\n<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBvt MG [[Nelson A. Miles]]\n[[File:IIcorpsbadge1.png|frameless|left]]\n| 1st Brigade\n<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol George W. Scott\n<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol George N. Macy\n|\n* [[26th Michigan Volunteer Infantry Regiment|26th Michigan]]: Cpt Lucius H. Ives\n* [[5th New Hampshire Volunteer Infantry|5th New Hampshire]] (battalion): Ltc Welcome A. Crafts\n* [[2nd New York Heavy Artillery Regiment|2nd New York Heavy Artillery]]: Maj Oscar F. Hulser\n* [[61st New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|61st New York]]: Maj George W. Schaffer\n* [[81st Pennsylvania Infantry|81st Pennsylvania]]: Ltc William Wilson\n* [[140th Pennsylvania Infantry|140th Pennsylvania]]: Cpt William A. F. Stockton\n|-\n| [[Irish Brigade (U.S.)|2nd Brigade]]\n<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Robert Nugent (officer)|Robert Nugent]]\n|\n* [[28th Regiment Massachusetts Volunteer Infantry|28th Massachusetts]] (5 companies): Cpt Patrick H. Bird\n* [[63rd New York Infantry|63rd New York]] (6 companies): Cpt William H. Terwilliger\n* [[69th Infantry Regiment (New York)|69th New York]]: Ltc James J. Smith\n* [[88th New York Infantry|88th New York]] (5 companies): Ltc Denis F. Burke\n* [[4th New York Heavy Artillery Regiment|4th New York Heavy Artillery]]: Maj Seward F. Gould\n|-\n| 3rd Brigade\n<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBvt BG Henry J. Madill ('''w''', April 2)\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBvt BG [[Clinton D. MacDougall]]\n|\n* [[7th New York Veteran Infantry Regiment|7th New York Veteran]]: Ltc Anthony Pokorny\n* [[39th New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|39th New York]]: Col Augustus Funk ('''w''