{"title_page": "1980 in marathon running", "text_new": "{{Disputed|date=June 2010}}\n\nThis page lists the '''World Best Year Performances''' in the year '''[[1980 in athletics (track and field)|1980]]''' in the '''[[marathon race|Marathon]]''' for both men and women. One of the main events during this season were the [[Athletics at the 1980 Summer Olympics|1980 Summer Olympics]] in [[Moscow]], [[Soviet Union]], where the final of the [[Athletics at the 1980 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's marathon|men's competition]] was held on Friday August 1, 1980. The competition had an entry list of 76 competitors, with 53 runners actually finishing the race.\n\nNorway's [[Grete Waitz]] clocked 2:25:41 winning the [[New York City Marathon]] on October 26, 1980, but her time was disputed and therefore not recognized as a world record because remeasurements of a nearly identical course in 1981 was 150 m short.<ref>https://www.arrs.run/MaraRank/ATM_Mara1980.htm</ref>\n\n==Men==\n\n===Records===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\" text-align:center; font-size:110%;\" width=\"95%\"\n|-\n!colspan=\"5\"|Standing records prior to the 1980 season in track and field\n|-\n| [[Marathon world record progression|World Record]] || {{flagathlete|[[Derek Clayton]]|AUS}} || '''2:08:33.6''' || May 30, 1969 || {{flagicon|BEL}} [[Antwerp, Belgium]] \n|}\n\n===1980 World Year Ranking===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\" text-align:center; font-size:110%;\" width=\"95%\"\n|-\n!Rank\n!Time\n!Athlete\n!Venue\n!Date\n!Note\n|- \n| 1 || '''2:09:01''' ||align=left| {{flagathlete|[[Gerard Nijboer]]|NED}} || Amsterdam, Netherlands || 26-05-1980 || [[Dutch records in athletics|NR]]\n|- \n| 2 || '''2:09:41''' ||align=left| {{flagathlete|[[Alberto Salazar]]|USA}} || New York, United States ||26-10-1980 ||\n|- \n| 3 || '''2:09:45''' ||align=left| {{flagathlete|[[Toshihiko Seko]]|JPN}} || Fukuoka, Japan || 07-12-1980 ||  \n|- \n| 4 || '''2:09:49''' ||align=left| {{flagathlete|[[Takeshi So]]|JPN}} || Fukuoka, 